Definition: To apply the mind to the acquisition of learning
To follow  educational or professional studies at a university
To make a close study of a subject
To be in doubt or perplexity
To apply one's mind to the acquiring of something
To be occupied with a specific branch of learning
To commit to memory and exercise oneself in the rendering
To scrutinize a visible object in order to ascertain its nature or to be familiar with or interpret its appearance
